thread.title: Scott Shafer: Eric Dungey, Ervin Philips 'ready to go' against South Florida
thread.title_full: Scott Shafer: Eric Dungey, Ervin Philips 'ready to go' against South Florida | syracuse.com

author: Nate Mink | nmink@syracuse.com
title: Scott Shafer: Eric Dungey, Ervin Philips 'ready to go' against South Florida
text:
Syracuse, N.Y. â€” Syracuse is expected to have two of its biggest offensive pieces return to the field Saturday at South Florida.
Freshman quarterback Eric Dungey (head) and hybrid back Ervin Philips (knee) are "ready to go" after practicing with the team Sunday, head coach Scott Shafer said on his weekly video interview posted on cuse.com.
"They're ready," Shafer said. "They've been running with the team all last week, practicing, and they look good. We got the offense rolling (Sunday) and there really was no hesitation.
"Erv made a nice cut on his leg and felt good about it, came back smiling to the huddle, 'Feel good, Coach,' and Eric made some real nice throws during practice."
Dungey, who took over the starting quarterback position in Week 2 following Terrel Hunt's season-ending Achilles injury, had missed the Sept. 26 loss against LSU because of a head injury.
Philips had missed the previous three games following knee surgery.
Kick time for Saturday's game at South Florida is scheduled for 3:30 p.m.
